%N A179583 Number of permutations of 1..n+8 with deficiencies #{i : p(i) < i} exceeding exceedances #{i : p(i) > i} by n or more.
%H A179583 R. J. Mathar, <a href="/A179583/b179583.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..30</a>, terms 1..20 from _R. H. Hardin_
%H A179583 M. F. Hasler and R. J. Mathar, <a href="/A179582/a179582_3.pdf">Hardin's exceedance excesses A179579-A179582</a>, July 2026.
%H A179583 <a href="/index/Rec#order_16">Index to entries of linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, order 16.
%F A179583 a(n) = 4^(n + 8) + 3^(n + 6)*(n - 11)*(n + 8)/2 + 2^(n + 1)*(n + 7)*(n + 8)*(n^2 - 53*n - 210)/3 + (n + 6)*(n + 7)*(n + 8)*(n^3 - 42*n^2 + 41*n + 1860)/720. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 18 2026
%F A179583 a(n) = A179582(n+1) + A179575(n). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 18 2026
%F A179583 G.f.: ( 26488 -654761*x +7476383*x^2 -52316741*x^3 +250895483*x^4 -873350472*x^5 +2279064706*x^6 -4538938086*x^7 +6953913296*x^8 -8193807152*x^9 +7363697904*x^10 -4956311840*x^11 +2418562176*x^12 -807860736*x^13 +165196800*x^14 -15593472*x^15 ) / ( (-1+4*x)*(-1+3*x)^3*(2*x-1)^5*(x-1)^7 ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 22 2026
%o A179583 (PARI) {A179583(n)=4^(n+8)+3^(n+6)*(n-11)*(n+8)\2+2^(n+1)*(n+7)*(n+8)*(n^2-53*n-210)/3+(n+6)*(n+7)*(n+8)*(n^3-42*n^2+41*n+1860)/720} \\ (same as formula). - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 20 2026
